[We must presume that the patient has survived. It may be that the
level of antibody generated by the primary immunisation was
protective. Alternatively the dog responsible for the bite may not
have been rabid. Whatever the explanation, travellers in India should
be aware of the existence of counterfeit medicines and should seek
treatment only from government-run pharmacies. - Mod.CP]
